49','','Verify Candidate`s application data',1,154),(224,'Selecting committee, System','System should support preparation of the examination for the major .\nMODULE: MOD3_UC3\nPreconditions: Selecting committee member is logged in to the system.\n','1. 	Selecting committee chooses to prepare an examination at a certain major .\n2. 	System presents a form with the data concerning place , time and additional information .\n3. 	Selecting committee provides the data about the examination .\n4. 	System stores the data and displays a confirmation message .\n','3.1 IF Provided data is before that day THEN System informs about the wrong date .\n',_binary '\0','Prepare an examination','2016-02-20 04:43:31','','Prepare an examination',1,154),(225,'Selecting committee, System','module: MOD4_UC1\nPreconditions: Selection committee member is logged in to the system','1. 	Selecting committee chooses the admission-statistics option .\n2. 	Selecting committee chooses one of the admissions from the available in the system .\n3. 	System presents general statistics concerning the number of applications submitted to all majors .\n\n','3.1 IF Selecting committee would like to check detailed statistics THEN Selecting committee chooses a major and selects a show-details option .\n3.1.2. 	System presents detailed information and graphs concerning the number of applications submitted to that major .',_binary '\0','Monitor number of applications','2016-02-20 04:46:29','','Monitor number of applications',1,154),(226,'Administrator, System','Administrator can monitor all the changes that were made in the system .\nmodule: MOD4_UC2\nPreconditions: Administrator is logged in to the system\n','1. 	Administrator chooses the preview-history option .\n2. 	Administrator provides search criteria for the change events in the system .\n3. 	System presents a list of all changes made in the system .\n4. 	Administrator selects an event and chooses a detailed view .\n5. 	System displays detailed information concerning the nature of the change and the user who performed the action . ','',_binary '\0','Monitor changes in the system','2016-02-20 04:48:41','','Monitor changes in the system',1,154),(227,'Administrator, System, Selecting committee ','Administrator and Selection committee can send message to the Candidates .\r\nMODULE: MOD4_UC3\r\nPreconditions: Administrator or Selection committee is logged in to the system.\r\n','1. 	Administrator or Selecting committee selects the send a message option .\r\n2. 	Administrator or Selecting committee selects Users from the list .\r\n3. 	Administrator or Selecting committee enters the message .\r\n4. 	Administrator or Selecting committee confirms sending the message .\r\n5. 	System sends the message to the User e-mail\r\n','2.A No User was selected.\r\n2.A.1.	System informs that at least one User should be selected .\r\n2.A.2.	Go back to step 2 .\r\n2.B The list of Users is empty and the actor is Administrator.\r\n2.B.1.	System shows option to add new User .\r\n2.B.2.	Use case finishes .\r\n3.A Entered message is empty.\r\n3.A.1.	System informs that message can not be empty .\r\n3.A.2.	System shows the template messages .\r\n3.A.3.	Administrator or Selection commitee chooses template .\r\n3.A.4.	System inserts template as message .\r\n3.A.5.	Go back to step 3 .',_binary '\0','Send a message to User','2016-02-18 22:52:52','','Send a message to User',1,154),(228,'Customer, Broker System',' login page loaded','1. Customer selects registration operation\r\n2. Broker System asks for Customer name, date of birth and address\r\n3. Customer enters registration information\r\n4. Broker System validates Customer information\r\n5. Broker System generate login information for Customer\r\n\r\n','4.a. Customer registration information is not valid \r\n4.a.1. Broker System displays registration failure page',_binary '\0','Register Customer','2016-03-17 09:42:36','','Register Customer',1,146),(229,'Administrator, User','Post a group message','1. Administrator logs on to the administration panel.\r\n2. Administrator selects the Post group message option.\r\n3. Administrator types the message and posts it.\r\n4. User receives the message when downloading new data.','',_binary '\0','Post a group message','2016-03-18 04:50:26','','Post a group message',1,155),(230,'Administrator','Configure the server','1. Administrator logs on to the administration panel.\r\n2. Administrator selects the Configure option.\r\n3. Administrator chooses and changes the desired settings.\r\n4. Administrator saves configuration settings.\r\n','4.a. Administrator cancels configuration changes.',_binary '\0','Configure the server','2016-03-18 03:57:01','','Configure the server',1,155),(231,'Administrator, System','Add a new channel group','1. Administrator logs on to the administration panel.\n2. System displays administration options.\n3. Administrator selects the Group and channel management option.\n4. System displays a list of defined channel groups and an add/delete group menu.\n5. Administrator types the name of a new group and selects Add group.\n6. System checks if a group with the given name has not been already defined and if so, inserts the name of a new group into a database.\n7. See step 4.','',_binary '\0','Add a new channel group','2016-03-18 10:01:22','','Add a new channel group',1,155),(232,'Administrator, System','Add a new channel','1. Administrator logs on to the administration panel.\r\n2. System displays administration options.\r\n3. Administrator selects the Group and channel management option.\r\n4. System displays a list of defined channel groups and an add/delete group menu.\r\n5. Administrator chooses a group to which he wants to add a new channel.\r\n6. System displays a list of channels in the selected group and an add/delete menu.\r\n7. Administrator types the name of the channel and the URL of the news service and selects Add channel.\r\n8. System checks if a channel with the given name or URL has not been already defined and if so, inserts the channel information into a database.\r\n9. System adds an information about the new channel to a group message.\r\n10. See step 6.\r\n11. Administrator selects the Finish option.\r\n12. System posts a group message containing information about all new channels in the selected channel group.\r\n','5.a. Administrator adds more channels. Proceed to step 7.',_binary '\0','Add a new channel','2016-03-18 04:08:39','','Add a new channel',1,155),(233,'Administrator, System','Delete a channel','1. Administrator logs on to the administration panel.\n2. System displays administration options.\n3. Administrator selects the Group and channel management option.\n4. System displays a list of defined channel groups and an add/delete group menu.\n5. Administrator chooses a group containing the channel he wants to delete.\n6. System displays a list of channels in the selected group and an add/delete menu.\n7. Administrator selects the channel(s) he wants to delete and chooses the Delete option.\n8. System deletes the selected channels from the database.\n9. System posts a group message containing information about the deleted channels in the selected channel group to all users involved (subscribing the deleted channels).\n10. System deletes all subscription information concerning the deleted channels.','',_binary '\0','Delete a channel','2016-03-18 12:14:04','','Delete a channel',1,155),(234,'Administrator,System','Delete a channel group','1. Administrator logs on to the administration panel.\n2. System displays administration options.\n3. Administrator selects the Group and channel management option.\n4. System displays a list of defined channel groups and an add/delete group menu.\n5. Administrator selects the group(s) he wants to delete and chooses the Delete option.\n6. System asks for confirmation.\n7. System deletes all channels from the selected groups (see: UC5, steps 8 to 10).','',_binary '\0','Delete a channel group','2016-03-18 12:16:28','','Delete a channel group',1,155),(235,'Administrator,System','Delete a user group','1. Administrator logs on to the administration panel.\r\n2. System displays administration options.\r\n3. Administrator selects the Delete users option.\r\n4. System displays the users deletion menu.\r\n5. Administrator selects deletion options (i.e. date of users` last login).\r\n6. Administrator confirms deletion request.\r\n7. System finds all users matching deletion criteria and deletes found user accounts.','6.a. Administrator cancels user deletion',_binary '\0','Delete a user group','2016-03-18 06:19:29','','Delete a user group',1,155),(236,'Daemon, System','Update news','1. Daemon sends a HTTP request to a defined news service.\n2. System receives a RSS-like formatted news file.\n3. System parses the received news file.\n4. System assigns an expiry date and time to each incoming message.\n5. System inserts appropriate parts of the news file into a news database.','',_binary '\0','Update news','2016-03-18 12:21:31','','Update news',1,155),(237,'System','Delete news','1. System queries the database for news messages, whose expiry date and time have passed.\n2. System deletes all returned messages from the database.','',_binary '\0','Delete news','2016-03-18 12:22:09','','Delete news',1,155),(238,'User, System','Register a new user','1. System asks the user if he/she wants to register.\r\n2. User confirms he/she wants to register.\r\n3. System sends a registration request to the server.\r\n4. Server creates a new user account and sends back a user ID.\r\n5. System stores the user ID and instructs the user how to subscribe news channels or configure his/her preferences. \r\n','4.a. User refuses to register.\r\n4.a.1 System displays an information that it cannot be used without prior registration.\r\n4.a.2 User confirms the message.\r\n4.a.3 System terminates.\r\n',_binary '\0','Register a new user','2016-03-18 00:32:22','','Register a new user',1,155),(239,'User, system','Download news','1. User chooses to update locally stored news.\n2. System sends a HTTP request to the Mobile News server.\n3. Server sends all pending group messages.\n4. Server sends separate news messages from all subscribed channels.\n5. System receives news messages and stores them in a local database.\n6. System displays a list of groups with subscribed channels and the number of new messages in each of them.','',_binary '\0','Download news','2016-03-18 12:33:57','Server','Download news',1,155),(240,'User, System','Run the application','1. User starts the application.\r\n2. System checks for registration information.\r\n3. If the user is already registered, the system automatically updates news messages from subscribed channels (refer to Download news use case). If no, the system attempts to register a new user (refer to Register a new user use case).','',_binary '\0','Run the application','2016-03-18 06:36:47','','Run the application',1,155),(241,'User, System','Subscribe/unsubscribe news channels','1. User chooses the Channel subscription option.\n2. System requests for and downloads a list of available groups and channels.\n3. System displays a tree view of available groups and channels and marks those already subscribed by the user.\n4. User selects the channels he/she wants to subscribe and/or deselects already subscribed channels to unsubscribe them and chooses the Change subscription options.\n5. System sends the subscription configuration to the Mobile News server and waits for confirmation.\n6. Server alters the user`s subscription configuration in a database and sends a change confirmation.\n7. System receives the confirmation and displays it.','',_binary '\0','Subscribe/unsubscribe news channels','2016-03-18 12:39:39','Server','Subscribe/unsubscribe news channels',1,155),(242,'User, System','Configure user preferences','1. User chooses the Preferences option.\n2. System displays a list of available options (i.e. font and colour settings, local news caching, etc..)\n3. User configures the option according to his/her preferences and confirm the changes.\n4. System saves user preferences configuration and displays main application view.','',_binary '\0','Configure user preferences','2016-03-18 12:46:12','','Configure user preferences',1,155),(243,'User, System','Read news','1. User chooses a news group from the Today menu.\n2. System displays a list of topics of available messages in chosen group.\n3. User chooses a topic.\n4. System displays the message using user`s appearance preferences.\n5. User reads the message and closes it or uses a hyperlink to go to the full message.\n6. System marks the message as Read.','',_binary '\0','Read news','2016-03-18 12:47:42','','Read news',1,155),(198,'Candidate, System','Candidate has to pay an application fee for each major he/she chooses .\r\nMODULE: MOD1_UC4: \r\nPreconditions:\r\n- Candidate is logged in to the system\r\n- Candidate has chosen at least one major','1. 	Candidate proceeds to the chosen-majors view .\r\n2. 	System presents list containing chosen majors .\r\n3. 	Candidate chooses a major that he/she wants to pay for .\r\n4. 	System presents a payment form and asks about the method of payment .\r\n5. 	Candidate chooses to use a credit card .\r\n6. 	Candidate provides credit card data and confirms payment .\r\n7. 	System presents updated list of the chosen majors .\r\n','5.A Candidate chooses to pay by money transfer.\r\n5.A.1.	System presents Candidate\'s individual account number .\r\n5.A.2.	Candidate performs money transfer ( outside the system ) .\r\n5.A.3.	As soon as as money are registered by System ( MOD2_UC12 ) Candidate can assign payment to the major ( if he/she do not do that, the payment will be assigned automatically according to priorities ) .\r\n5.A.4.	Use cases finishes .',_binary '\0','Assign an application fee to a major','2016-02-19 14:41:18','','Assign an application fee to a major',1,154);
